## LIVE FINDINGS (telnet, NE-77, 2026-07-01)
- **The node enumerates NOTHING.** Every RTRV returns current state only:
  RTRV-OPMODE = the one current MXP string; RTRV-OTU4C2 = FREQ=1530.33 single
  value (GRIDLESS=DISABLE); RTRV-PPM = **DENY IICM** (verb does not exist).
  → Option catalog for the wizard MUST come from this file/docs. Node supplies
  current state + physical-optic presence + post-apply verification only.
- **AID grammar (confirmed):** card `SLOT-2-6`; trunk pluggable `PPM-2-6-{11,12}`;
  client pluggable `APPM-2-6-{port}`; trunk facility `VFAC-2-6-{port}-1` (OTU4C2);
  client facility `AGGR-2-6-{port}-1` (100GIGE); opmode on `SLOT-2-6`.
- **Port population on SLOT-2-6:** 5=QSFP-4X10G optic; 7=QSFP-100G optic +
  AGGR-2-6-7-1 IS-NR; 8 & 9 = PPM container but NO optic, no facility (OOS-AUMA,UAS);
  10 = no PPM. Trunk 11 IS-NR (FREQ=1530.33, circuit engltodenv up), 12 OOS.
- **Parse note:** provisioned lines end `...:IS-NR,` (trailing comma); unpopulated
  end `...:OOS-AUMA,UAS` (no trailing comma). RTRV-EQPT::ALL paginates with a `>`
  continuation and repeats the `M <ctag> COMPLD` header per page.
- Trunk facility full param set (RTRV-OTU4C2): FEC=SD-25-DE-OFF, OSFBER=1E-5,
  OSDBER=1E-7, FREQ, LOSSB=DWDM, SQUELCHMODE=ODU-AIS, PORTMODE=DWDM-TRANS-AIS,
  GRIDLESS=DISABLE. Client (RTRV-100GIGE): MTU, NUMOFLANES=4, SOAK.

## DENY codes + preconditions (telnet 2026-07-03)
- `SDBE` "Facility Is Not Provisioned" — RTRV/DLT on an absent facility. This is
  the "available, not yet provisioned" signal (→ wizard offers **create**).
- `IDNV` "PPM Does Not Exist" — ENT-100GIGE on a client port with **no physical
  optic**. **Precondition: a 100G optic must be physically present** (APPM line
  has a 100G CARDNAME) before a 100GIGE facility can be created. PPM-1 container
  being EQUIP is NOT enough.
- `IICM` "Invalid MOD1" — verb/modifier not supported (e.g. RTRV-PPM).
- Consequence for live testing: ports 8/9 (no optic) and 10 (no PPM) cannot be
  built out without inserting optics. Port 7 is currently the ONLY client port
  with a 100G optic, and it is already provisioned (IS-NR). To exercise a full
  build-from-scratch, either tear down & rebuild port 7, or insert optics in 8/9/10.

